---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../config';
---
<Base title="Privacy policy · Pillot" description="Pillot is built so that your medication information stays with you.">
  <article class="container prose">
    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="effective">Effective date: July 6, 2026</p>

    <p>Pillot is built so that your medication information stays with you. This policy explains exactly what that means.</p>

    <h2>What stays on your phone</h2>
    <p>Every medication you add, your schedule, your reminders, your dose history, and your notes are stored locally on your iPhone. We don't have a server that holds this information, and we can't see it, because it never reaches us.</p>

    <h2>The one thing that briefly leaves your phone</h2>
    <p>When you scan a prescription label, Pillot sends a photo of that label over an encrypted connection so it can be read and turned into a digital label. That photo is used only for that purpose. Once the label is read, the photo is discarded. We do not retain label photos on our servers, and we do not use them for anything other than reading the label you scanned.</p>

    <h2>Accounts</h2>
    <p>Pillot doesn't have accounts. There's nothing to sign up for, no username or password, and no profile tied to your identity anywhere in our systems.</p>

    <h2>Notifications</h2>
    <p>Reminders are scheduled and delivered locally by your iPhone, using the times you set. They don't pass through our servers or anyone else's.</p>

    <h2>Analytics and tracking</h2>
    <p>Pillot doesn't use analytics tools, advertising identifiers, or third-party trackers. We don't know how you use the app, and we're not trying to find out.</p>

    <h2>Data sale</h2>
    <p>We don't sell data. We don't have any to sell.</p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>Pillot is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect information from children.</p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>If this policy changes, we'll update the effective date above. Material changes will be reflected here before they take effect.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about this policy or how Pillot handles information can be sent to <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  article {
    padding-block: 48px 24px;
  }

  .effective {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 2em;
  }
</style>
